Good Old Software License (GOSL) v1.0

Inspired by the era when software was built by enthusiasts:  
useful, unbloated, free, and respectful of users.  
  
This license ensures that software remains free of charge under its license terms,  
modifiable, and shareable, while preventing monetization of the Software itself, 
advertising, telemetry, and subscription models.

Copyright (c) 2026 THONGVAN Alexis

For the purposes of this license, 'monetization of the Software' means: 
  
  a) charging any fee for the Software itself or any portion of its functionality
  b) gating Software features behind payment
  c) embedding advertising within the Software.
  It does NOT mean: charging for services, training, 
  support, documentation, hardware bundles, or outputs produced using the Software, 
  provided the Software itself remains freely obtainable under this license.

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy
of this Software and associated documentation files (the "Software"), to use,
copy, modify, merge, publish, and distribute the Software, subject to the
following conditions:

1. The Software may be used for any lawful purpose, including internal use within
   companies and organizations.

2. The Software, and any derivative works based on the Software, may NOT be:

   a) sold or licensed for a fee
   b) integrated, bundled, linked, or incorporated as a component of 
      a product that is sold or redistributed for value. Running the 
      Software on servers to provide a service does not, by itself, 
      constitute incorporation as a component.
   c) redistributed in a form that includes monetization mechanisms 
      such as microtransactions, paid feature unlocks, or subscription gating

3. Any redistribution of the Software, including modified versions or
   derivative works, must be provided free of charge and must include 
   this license and all original copyright notices.

4. For clarity, internal use of the Software by an organization that
   generates revenue does not constitute monetization of the Software.
   Use of the Software as a tool to produce outputs (documents, media, data, etc.) 
   that are commercialized is permitted, provided the Software itself is not sold, 
   sublicensed, or incorporated as a component of a commercial product.
   
5. Software Integrity Requirements

   Any software distributed under this license, including modified
   versions or derivative works, must NOT include:

   a) mechanisms that collect, transmit, or expose usage data, 
      behavioral data, or system information to any party other 
      than the user operating the Software. 
      
      Standard operating system interactions (file I/O, 
      network requests explicitly initiated by user actions, 
      inter-process communication required for the Software's 
      stated functionality) are not considered telemetry.
      Crash reporting, diagnostic reporting, and usage analytics 
      are only permitted when explicitly enabled by the user for 
      that specific transmission.

   b) advertising of any kind

   c) subscription mechanisms, paywalls, feature unlocking through
      payment, or any other form of monetized access

      Requesting voluntary donations is permitted, provided that all
      Software functionality remains fully available without payment.

6. Any distribution of modified versions of the Software must be 
   licensed exclusively under the terms of this license, and must 
   include or provide access to the complete corresponding source 
   code under the same license terms.
   
7. Forks and derivative works must follow the conditions of this
   license and must not claim to be the original project or an
   official release of the original project without explicit
   permission from the original copyright holder(s).
   
   For the purposes of this license, 'derivative works' refers to modified 
   versions of the Software itself, not to separate programs that interact with, 
   invoke, or use the Software's outputs.

8. Donation Integrity

   Redistribution of the Software, including modified versions or
   derivative works, must not be performed solely or primarily for the
   purpose of redirecting voluntary donations to a different recipient.

   Forks and derivative works that introduce substantial modifications
   may request donations for their own development, provided they do not
   misrepresent themselves as the original project or an official release.
   
   Substantial modifications means the addition of significant new functionality, 
   architectural changes, or a sustained development effort distinct from 
   the original project — not cosmetic changes, rebranding, translations, 
   or minor bug fixes.

